<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-225-058 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 406 532</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Feb 8 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Hotelecopy files lawsuit against U.S. Postal Service. (attemptingto recover $5.25 million in losses after fax machines were pulledfrom US Post Offices)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hotelecopy Inc. (Joint ventures).andO;Ticker:    FAXM.andO;Topic:     Joint VentureFacsimileUnited States. Postal Service.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>HOTELECOPY FILES LAWSUIT AGAINST U.S.andP;  POSTAL SERVICE 02/08/91 MIAMI,FLORIDA, U.S.A., 1991 FEB 8 (NB) -- Hotelecopy, which had its fax machinespulled from U.S.andP;  Post Offices early in the month after its FaxMail deal wentsour, filed suit against the U.S.andP;  Postal Service to recover its $5.25million in losses.andP;  Postal officials previously rejected Hotelecopy's October23 claim citing Postal Service non-compliance with its obligations to providemerchandising and awareness support for the FaxMail Program.andP;  Claimingdefault for non-payment of rentals, the Postal Service terminated the jointventure.andM;&quot;While Hotelecopy met its contractual agreement, to provide and supporthighly sophisticated self-service, credit-card operated facsimile terminalsin 265 post offices nationwide, the U.S.andP;  Postal Service demanded largerental payments, even though they breached our contract by failure to providethe promotion and support necessary for the program's success,&quot; HotelecopyChairman Edd Helms explained.andP;  &quot;The U.S.andP;  Postal Service failed to meet itsobligations but they expected us to continue to pay,&quot; he said.andP;  Helms claimed82% of customers were happy with FaxMail, based on Postal Service figures.andM;Helms added that the Post Office placed &quot;service discontinued&quot; signs on mostFaxMail units February 1, before they were due to be pulled from service.andO;The joint venture continues to operate in the Midwest, where 44 machines areinstalled in post offices in Chicago, St. Louis and Denver.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19910208/Press Contact: Stanley Fields, Hotelecopy, Inc.,andO;800-765-3334)</TEXT></DOC>